               <summary>This is a palm leaf manuscript that contains what is considered as the first chapter of <persName xml:lang="sa">Vedānta Deśikaṉ</persName>'s magnum opus, the Rahasyatrayasāra (in manipravalam).
The title <term xml:lang="sa"><quote>Prapanna pārijātam</quote></term> is also found on the cover leaf, but has been subsequently struck out with a pencil (?)</summary><msItem defective="false" class="#pirapantam"><title xml:lang="ta">Guruparamparāsāram <term xml:lang="en">with commentary</term></title><author xml:lang="ta">Vedānta Deśika <term xml:lang="en">and anonymous commentator</term></author><textLang mainLang="tam" otherLangs="san"/><incipit xml:lang="ta"><pb facs="5" n="1r"/>     
<lb n="1"/>śrīmate śrīnivāsamahādeśikāya namaḥ śrīmate śrīnivāsarāmānujamahādeśikāya namaḥ śrīmate vedāntarāmānujamahādeśikāya namaḥ śrīmate gopālāryyamahādeśikāya namaḥ jñānavairā<unclear>gyānuṣṭhāna</unclear> <lb n="2"/><unclear>śevadhaye</unclear>  śrīmate vedāntarāmānujamahādeśikāya namaḥ sākṣānnārāyanan devam asmad rakaṣaika dīkṣayā | avatīrṇamavandyāṃ śrīraṅganāthaguruṃ bhaje | 
<lb n="3"/>śrīmadvedāntaguror natvā śrīguruparamparāsāraṃ | vyākaravāṇi grūṇām ājñāparavān satāṃprasādāya |<unclear>trayyanta s</unclear>rū sarasoktiṣaṃ cāpalān menemandasya sāhasa maṃ<lb n="4"/>dīrṇamidaṃ sahantāṃ | santo dayārdṛhradayair na sahaya eva ghar? gunassapadi viṣṇupadī vigāhaḥ</incipit><explicit xml:lang="ta"><pb facs="34" n="29v"/>   
<lb n="6"/><gap reason="ellipsis"/>ōriṭattil pradhānamakac colliyiruntālum mūṉṟi maṅgasiddhi yuṇṭe- 
<lb n="7"/>ṉṟaikkum pradarśanavaraṃ |
śrīmate śrīnivāsamahādeśikāya namaḥ - śrīmate śrīnivāsarāmānujamahādeśikā namaḥ - śrīmate vedāntarāmānujamahādeśikāya namaḥ - śrīmate gopālāryyamahādeśikāya namaḥ -<lb n="8"/>jñānavairā<unclear>gyānuṣṭhāna</unclear> <unclear>śevadhaye</unclear>  śrīmate vedāntarāmānujamahādeśikāya namaḥ - śrīmate nigamānta mahādeśikāya namaḥ - </explicit></msItem></msContents>
